==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Antialbumid
<hw>An`ti*al*bu"mid</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>anti-</ets> + <ets>-albumin</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A body formed from albumin by pancreatic and gastric
digestion. It is convertible into antipeptone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antialbumose</ent>⟦br⟧
